Rationale: The regex `BUG-[0-9]+` requires a pure numeric suffix and never matches
the severity-prefix IDs `BUG-H1`, `BUG-M3`, `BUG-L6` generated by QFB Phase 3.

Fix: Extend the regex to match both formats:
  - `BUG-([HML]|[0-9])[0-9]*` — accepts BUG-H1, BUG-M3, BUG-L6 AND BUG-001, BUG-123
  - Also relaxes format-policing patterns (wrong_headings, deep_headings, etc.) to
    match BUG- generically rather than requiring numeric suffix.
  - At line 313: `BUG-([HML][0-9]+|[0-9]+)` extracts both formats for iteration.

This fix also requires updating SKILL.md:1615 to show both ID format examples:
  "### BUG-NNN (e.g., BUG-001 or BUG-H1)" rather than "BUG-001" alone.
